Class ServiceBay

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.garage.model.service_garage.ServiceBay
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    HybridElectricBay

    public class ServiceBay
extends java.lang.Object
    The ServiceBay class holds all the functionalities of the service bay such as occupying or releasing a vehicle in a service bay.
    Author:
    jhnguye4

    • Method Detail

      • startBayNumberingAt101

        public static void startBayNumberingAt101()
        Static method. Resets the service bay numbering to start from 1 (so the next 3 bays added for this project would have numbers/IDs E01, 102, and 103).

      • occupy

        public void occupy(Vehicle v)
            throws BayOccupiedException,
                   BayCarMismatchException
        Occupies the service bay with the given vehicle. Throws a BayOccupiedException if the service bay is already occupied.
        Parameters:
        v - is the vehicle that the bay will occupy
        Throws:
        BayOccupiedException - if the service bay is already occupied.
        BayCarMismatchException - if the vehicle is not the correct vehicle for the bay.
